readme:
Service Usage

Following biometric enrolment of a client record from offshore, BMS will notify CDH. As a strategic measure, this service will also include information about onshore biometric collections, namely, Detention, ONPRO, Citizenship and ISR sourced facial images caseloads. This service includes the enrolment data but not the FCC data.

Service Behaviour

Data is captured by CEP, stored by Leida, transmitted to CDH and subsequently presented to CSP.
CSP captures the required data and sends to BAMS to consume using SV398.
BAMS then sends data using SV540 to CDH
CDH then sends data using SV563 to CSP for display.
